## 2026-03-29 - No generator configuration comparison
- Added A/B compare mode to `TypeScaleConfigEditor`. A toggle button labeled "A/B" appears next to the "Scale ratio" label. When enabled, a two-column layout shows Config A (current) and Config B (alternate) with full ratio preset lists and custom inputs in each column, plus side-by-side staircase editors for visual comparison. "Use B (ratio)" applies B's ratio and exits compare mode. A swap button (⇄) exchanges A and B ratios. Compare mode is purely local — no state leaks to the parent; only "Use B" triggers `onChange`. Initializes B to the next preset above A's current ratio for an immediately useful comparison.
- Files changed: `packages/figma-plugin/src/ui/components/generators/TypeScaleGenerator.tsx` ~L171
- **Learnings for future iterations:**

